>  What are the differences with the vesafb driver ??, speed ?, can I change
> resolutions without needing to reboot ? May I use the in/out RCA
> conectors, at least the out one to make Presentations with the notebook?
With native drivers you can change modes after booting if the card
supports it (Most can). It most likely with use the cards accel functions
to eliminate the latency problems that vesafb for fbcon has. 
